  abstract = {In the environment, the lapse rate of temperature and the relative humidity are prescribed. At the top of the downdraft column, the temperature, relative humidity, vertical air velocity, and the phase and size distribution of the precipitation particles are prescribed. With lapse rates of temperature approaching the dry-adiabatic value, even very light precipitation can drive intense downdrafts.As the stability of the thermal stratification is increased, progressively higher precipitation contents and eventually high precipitation contents in the form of ice are needed to drive intense downdrafts. A size distribution of precipitation particles having a relative abundance of smaller particles also favors intense downdrafts. The downdraft can be driven solely below cloud base provided the cloud delivers the necessary precipitation at its base. A comparison with available meager observations of wet downbursts lends support to these results. -from Author},
